## 🐛 Bug Report

The WorkbookReader 'worksheet' event seems to a wrong worksheet name

Lib version: 4.3.0

## Steps To Reproduce

- Use the following test function to load an excel file

```javascript
    static readFileStream(file) {
        return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
            const result = {};

            const readerOptions = {
                entries: 'emit',
                sharedStrings: 'cache',
                hyperlinks: 'cache',
                styles: 'cache',
                worksheets: 'emit',
            };

            const reader = new ExcelJS.stream.xlsx.WorkbookReader(file, readerOptions);

            reader.on('worksheet', (worksheetReader) => {
                const sheetName = worksheetReader.name;
                console.log('[readFileStream] worksheet created – name:', sheetName, '| id:', worksheetReader.id);

                const headers = [];
                const rows = [];

                worksheetReader.on('row', (row) => {
                    const { values } = row;
                    const cells = Array.isArray(values) ? values.slice(1) : [];
                    // console.log(`[readFileStream]   row #${row.number} –`, cells.map((v, i) => `col${i}: ${v}`).join(', '));

                    if (row.number === 1) {
                        cells.forEach((v, i) => {
                            headers[i] = v != null ? String(v) : '';
                        });
                    } else {
                        rows.push(cells);
                    }
                });

                worksheetReader.on('end', () => {
                    result[sheetName] = { headers, rows };
                    console.log('[readFileStream] worksheet done –', sheetName, '| headers:', headers, '| dataRows:', rows.length);
                });
            });

            reader.on('end', () => {
                console.log('[readFileStream] all done – result keys:', Object.keys(result));
                resolve(result);
            });

            reader.on('error', (err) => {
                reject(err);
            });

            reader.read().catch(reject);
        });
    }
```

## The expected behaviour:

- Logs should be:

[readFileStream] worksheet created – name: Article | id: 1
[readFileStream] worksheet created – name: Extended attributes | id: 2
[readFileStream] worksheet created – name: Color data | id: 3
[readFileStream] worksheet created – name: Test summary | id: 4
[readFileStream] worksheet created – name: Detail quality tests | id: 5
[readFileStream] worksheet created – name: Tables | id: 6
[readFileStream] worksheet created – name: Index | id: 7
[readFileStream] worksheet created – name: -Info- | id: 7

- Instead of
readFileStream] worksheet created – name: Sheet1 | id: 1
[readFileStream] worksheet created – name: Sheet2 | id: 2
[readFileStream] worksheet created – name: Sheet3 | id: 3
[readFileStream] worksheet created – name: Sheet4 | id: 4
[readFileStream] worksheet created – name: Sheet5 | id: 5
[readFileStream] worksheet created – name: Sheet6 | id: 6
[readFileStream] worksheet created – name: Sheet7 | id: 7

- In attachment there is the file i tried to load (created with ExcelJS)

